---

Reviewed by Opus 4.7 via manual /review-crate invocation (batched
multi-crate request; tick.sh was not used). Inspected 32 .rs files
under src/, Cargo.toml, README.md, DESIGN.md, .github/workflows/ci.yml.

Key findings:
- No build.rs, no proc-macro, no Command/network/include_bytes!
- 227 `unsafe` occurrences but most are `unsafe fn` decls with
  rustdoc `# Safety` (SIMD/Teddy intrinsics over __m128i/__m256i/
  uint8x16_t); core algorithm code (dfa/nfa/automaton) uses only
  `unsafe trait Automaton` + `unsafe impl` with justifying comments
- Several `unsafe { ... }` call sites in packed/teddy/builder.rs
  (lines 482, 546, 618, 748) and the dozens of test fixtures in
  packed/vector.rs lack the literal `// SAFETY:` prefix even though
  the feature-detection guard immediately above IS the safety
  invariant
- CI does not run miri (.github/workflows/ci.yml runs cargo test on
  matrix of OS/arch/Rust versions, no miri job)
- Pure-Rust unsafe (e.g. packed/ext.rs::distance, packed/pattern.rs::
  is_equal_raw call) is miri-testable; SIMD intrinsics are not
- Author: BurntSushi (Andrew Gallant), license Unlicense OR MIT
- Rating: neutral (capped by missing literal SAFETY comments per
  rubric §2; neutral dominates the §3 cap of positive).
